-> What is Class?
    - Class is a name group of property of functions.
    - Class name by convention is Capitalised.
    - Class is Logical Construct, a blue print.

-> What is Objects?
    - Object is the instance of the class.
    - It is something that actually accommodates some memory.
    - it is a physical thing.

-> "new" keywords
    - The keyword is used to make Objects.
    - Dynamically allocates memory and return a reference to it.

-> One of the Most important concept...
    - If lets say I have a class named Student ( See the Implementations as well ).
    - inside that class I have default rollNumber = 56
    - and in the Main Class I will set Roll Number to 36.
      which roll number will be stored?
      One that has set to Main Class..
      if it would have been null in that case it would have shown the roll number that is inside the *Parent Class*.

-> "this" keywords
    - It is like a placeholder for object.

-> Why Primitives are not initialised with "new" keywords?
    - They are not because they are directly stored in stack memory and it makes java more faster

-> If
    Class a = new Class();
    Class b = a;
    will changes made in a will also change that property in b?

    yes! because both of them internally are point towards the same object

-> Final keyword
    - final don't allow to change / modify object.
    - it only works for primitive
    - if
        final int a = 10;
        a = 100 (This is going to create error)

        final Student kush = new Student("Alex");
        kush.name = "Kush Makwana"; ( this is allowed )
        kush = new Student("Amrut"); ( this is not )
